<br>
At the moment, I have about 115 dual weild, 130 double attack and 128 (will be 130 easy soon) 1hs. I had planned on just going with the setup I have now and then switching to various weapons my skills cap out and for now just level care free.<br>
<br>
I also have only about 53 2hb skill and absolutly 0 2hs skill. I have an argent defender (or is that protecter? It's 33/49 2hs) and a sarnak battlehammer (30/40 2hb). Skills for those weapons go up very slow and I know they won't get any faster but I figure I will have plenty of time in the 40s to max them where as right now I might as well just use my best skill to level as fast as possible.<br>
<br>
But what if another skill will out damage the one I use now? I love to see crits for 110 with the sarnak hammer and double hits of 60. Still, I have to go through some misses to get any effect out of it.<br>
<br>
So, should I wait out till I level and use the guaranteed thing for now or try to switch out for the 2 handers to do some real damage but suffer from low skill for quite some time? Is the pain of &quot;miss miss miss&quot; gonna pay off when I'm in my 30s triple/quad hitting? <br>
<br>
As far as taunt goes, I don't really care. My shaman pal is tough and can take a few hits to root a mob and even after doing so on an add 3 times and healing me some 10 times, I can instantly get aggro from him.<br>
<br>
Another interesting question is should I give up the damage ratio and skill lead my sarnak battlehammer has and use my argent for when I managed to bag myself a wingblade or other nice 2hs? I find that most of the good 2 handers are slashers. The only weapon that would really need 2hb is the ToD but I already have a shaman slowing with me pretty much all the time.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=slammerp>Slammerp</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(11/16/02 10:59:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4417.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: 2hander or not at my level?</span><hr size=1> I used 1hb,and 1hs all the way to 47,then i switched to 2hs it was a like 5 LOL..The best way i know how i can tell u to get the skill up is to have a chanter &quot;BOON&quot; u and with all the dex that it gives u your 2hs will go up VERY fast.. all i can really tell ya bro.. just my 2cps worth.. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.geocities.com/eqphotolog/slam2banner.txt"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> </p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showPrevMessage?topicID=4417.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showNextMessage?topicID=4417.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthebunker.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4417.topic&index=1><img src=http://www.steelwarrior.org/forum/swaddreply.GIF border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a>